==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*xatis-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[heti]], Old High German [[haz]] (German [[Haß]]), Old Norse [[hatr]] (Swedish [[hat#Swedish|hat]]), Gothic [[𐌷𐌰𐍄𐌹𐍃]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈhete/}}

===Noun===
'''hete''' {{m}} (plural '''[[hetas]]''')
# [[hatred]], [[malice]]

===Derived terms===
*[[heteniþ|hetenīþ]]

===Descendants===
*English [[hate]] ''(noun)''

